If a user extends this configuration and set only the `fix` of the rule, then the inherited `options` is overrided by the default rule `options`.

```json
{
  "extends": ["shared.json"],
  "linter": {
    "enabled": true,
    "rules": {
      "style": {
        "useNamingConvention": {
          "level": "on",
          "fix": "none"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This basically results in the following merged config:

```json
{
  "extends": ["shared.json"],
  "linter": {
    "enabled": true,
    "rules": {
      "style": {
        "useNamingConvention": {
          "level": "on",
          "fix": "none",
          "options": {}
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

